$SPY $DJIA Rhetoric is changing, even Mike Wilson is changing his tune and he's been on the biggest bears on the Street for awhile. The economic data is starting to practically scream that inflation is beginning to come under control from the Feds measures. CPI is remaining high because of rent prices, those are laggard data points and generally take 9-12 months to roll over and they make up about 30% of the CPI data. There's many economic signals going off right now that inflation is about to come down pretty quickly in the next 12 months. Now the challenge is for the Fed to realize that and not overdo it. I expect .75 bps in November and 0.50 bps in December and that should be it, that's all it will take.   
  
At that point the Fed needs to allow the Fed Rate to work itself into the economy more because the M2 and M2V clearly show that the American/Global consumer is not going to be the cause of inflation staying sticky. Bullish

$SPY $DJIA You want a reason to be bullish? Take a look at the M2 and M2V. The money supply has peaked and the velocity of money is at the slowest rate it has been at since 1931... let me repeat that 1931!!! 
 
Now why is that bullish and not bearish? It's bullish because our financial institutions are still strong, unlike 1931. It's bullish because employment is still strong and the reduction in the M2V shows that a soft landing is doable. What it will require is for the Fed to stop in December, let home prices and rents roll over (which they've already started to), continue to reduce the balance sheet. 
 
This inflation isn't necessarily a result of the US consumer or global consumer, this is man made through the Feds negligence in over stimulating the economy. The M2V shows that this isn't the consumers fault and if the M2V can remain low, which it will at these interest rate levels, the M2 can remain stable or drop.. then we may be able to achieve a soft landing economically. Bullish
